<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-03-19T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-03-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="1160" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1160">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.516/164</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Ambassador <persName type="to">Fletcher</persName>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 40</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-03-19">
                                    <hi rend="italic">March 19, 1917</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to the Department’s telegram
                            No. 654, of February 6, 1917, addressed to Mr. Parker, directing him to
                            lodge a protest with the <hi rend="italic">de facto</hi> Government of
                            Mexico against its apparent purpose to force into liquidation the
                            National Bank of Mexico and the Bank of London and Mexico, there is
                            enclosed herewith, for your information, a translation of a note, dated
                            March 13, 1917, from the French Ambassador at this Capital, from which
                            it appears that further forced loans have been exacted from the National
                            Bank of Mexico.</p>
                        <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Robert Lansing</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>